div.p:
—both sides have accomplished their vital aims in the specific negotiations and
                    neither side has significantly prejudiced either crucial interests of the other
                    or the longer-term scenario for East-West relations in Europe;

—the product of these negotiations has taken the form of a limited albeit
                    important modus vivendi rather than a qualitative change in the nature of
                    East-West relations;

—a certain political balance has been reached which has both enhanced stability
                    and security in Europe and accorded a heightened measure of legitimacy to the
                    international system;
